<pageBreakToken id="DF72F7EE6A578090AA33838CB5579DB2" pageId="3" pageNumber="100" start="start">Diagnosis</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="142A5587A29154F81CE398CAFAE11395" pageId="3" pageNumber="100">
Like 
<taxonomicName id="11923763060B08F0073A1C9035442B6C" authorityName="Cav" authorityYear="1799" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum pygmaeum" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pygmaeum">
<emphasis id="BB3A505F089A0259E2AF87E39F08A557" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="100">Solanum pygmaeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cav., but differing in having mostly 1-branched inflorescences with 6-15 flowers, anthers &lt;3.5 mm long, strongly recurving fruiting pedicels, and berries &lt;1 cm in diameter with fewer than 30 seeds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
