<subSubSection id="B8290B3CC30ADF36CF9B93C9214A4BA2" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C829B38D276DA3016950BCB714F193E3" pageId="7" pageNumber="104">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DEC08E7A25B3F87E41964D1C8BD3D888" pageId="7" pageNumber="104">
<taxonomicName id="0AE14F6E77664E8F45EF8872FA5D4912" authorityName="Saerkinen &amp; M. Nee" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum rhizomatum" order="Solanales" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhizomatum">
<emphasis id="03F6C5C81E7E84626FBCB3DC3EC4073A" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="104">Solanum rhizomatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="EE85BD787D88E2B6A4E846617D0D82F6" authorityName="Cav" authorityYear="1799" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum pygmaeum" order="Solanales" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pygmaeum">
<emphasis id="C7539449FF07B93D9A36C86319068B0A" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="104">Solanum pygmaeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from central and coastal Argentina (see 
<bibRefCitation id="6E8145A8682C996419F08B31AE6FB118" author="Barboza, GE" journalOrPublisher="Flora Argentina: Flora Vascular de la Republica Argentina, Dicotyledoneae, Solanaceae" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" pagination="231 - 264" refId="B3" refString="Barboza, GE, Knapp, S, Saerkinen, T, 2013. Solanum Grupo VII. Moreloide. Flora Argentina: Flora Vascular de la Republica Argentina, Dicotyledoneae, Solanaceae Vol. 13: 231 - 264" title="Solanum Grupo VII. Moreloide." volume="Vol. 13" year="2013">Barboza et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
), another rhizomatous species of 
<taxonomicName id="C6DDD2C91F22B496827322629A5D1765" authority="Solanum" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum subsp. section" order="Solanales" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Solanum" species="pygmaeum" subSpecies="section">Solanum section Solanum</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="CBE4D9789006EB3EDDFACE7279D3545A" authorityName="Saerkinen &amp; M. Nee" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum rhizomatum" order="Solanales" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhizomatum">
<emphasis id="7B23371161FA4079F99779A93FEA04CB" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="104">Solanum rhizomatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="0D53A4A13513F9C4140B6463563BDB96" authorityName="Cav" authorityYear="1799" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum pygmaeum" order="Solanales" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pygmaeum">
<emphasis id="48B05E0966F1A5E4B63F663665094D65" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="104">Solanum pygmaeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having mostly 1-branched inflorescences with 6-15 flowers, anthers 3.2-3.5 mm long, strongly recurving fruiting pedicels, and berries with 15-25 seeds, while 
<taxonomicName id="4D65DD2033F67D0849AC0B5800107B36" authorityName="Cav" authorityYear="1799" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum pygmaeum" order="Solanales" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pygmaeum">
<emphasis id="D6B0D6417201DC725215F04350EF5FBA" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="104">Solanum pygmaeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
always has simple (unbranched) inflorescences with 2-6 flowers, anthers usually&gt;3.5 mm long, fruiting pedicels that are broadly spreading, and berries with&gt;50 seeds. Although these sets of characters overlap to some extent, 
<taxonomicName id="BCF4385B07740ABD534D0B2D81026E96" authorityName="Cav" authorityYear="1799" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum pygmaeum" order="Solanales" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pygmaeum">
<emphasis id="0AD4C4EA1B405DAA824E3CAC99CC4414" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="104">Solanum pygmaeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
individuals are generally smaller than those of 
<taxonomicName id="BFA95B5A70586A6083185D2D47CD8FB8" authorityName="Saerkinen &amp; M. Nee" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum rhizomatum" order="Solanales" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhizomatum">
<emphasis id="1F030E9B28E3C3DF968038595CF40EFB" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="104">Solanum rhizomatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(10-20 cm tall), with smaller leaves 1-5 cm long and 0.5-2.2 cm wide, while 
<taxonomicName id="26E65FD316B58A4B610737BA5BA443FA" authorityName="Saerkinen &amp; M. Nee" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum rhizomatum" order="Solanales" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhizomatum">
<emphasis id="780DAD22923FDE03C86E40AC2FFD18B0" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="104">Solanum rhizomatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows 15-50 cm tall, with larger leaves 2.3-8.0 cm long and 1.2-4.3 cm wide. 
<taxonomicName id="CDC0A636F42909D8D3F2B6FEE88B4DD4" authorityName="Cav" authorityYear="1799" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum pygmaeum" order="Solanales" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pygmaeum">
<emphasis id="BD5EB2472BCCB887DCE348E34ADF79A4" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="104">Solanum pygmaeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms dense colonies in secondary habitats such as railroad sidings, and has been introduced and naturalised in Europe and North America, presumably in boats carrying wool from eastern coastal Argentina (
<bibRefCitation id="B1AD779C7C271B32957CFC8B6B1B4BF5" author="Barboza, GE" journalOrPublisher="Flora Argentina: Flora Vascular de la Republica Argentina, Dicotyledoneae, Solanaceae" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" pagination="231 - 264" refId="B3" refString="Barboza, GE, Knapp, S, Saerkinen, T, 2013. Solanum Grupo VII. Moreloide. Flora Argentina: Flora Vascular de la Republica Argentina, Dicotyledoneae, Solanaceae Vol. 13: 231 - 264" title="Solanum Grupo VII. Moreloide." volume="Vol. 13" year="2013">Barboza et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="15EC74B30722D8723BA3228BA4C2038F" pageId="7" pageNumber="104">
As in many species of 
<taxonomicName id="76AAACF0E666CBCF441F518C76D01D54" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum" order="Solanales" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="67B277B0E7A31CEBD5725CC40CA7F99D" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="104">Solanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, variation in corolla colour occurs in 
<taxonomicName id="3C6B378EEED5D181B49A2ECE607433E4" authorityName="Saerkinen &amp; M. Nee" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum rhizomatum" order="Solanales" pageId="7" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhizomatum">
<emphasis id="C5B1E347CF1869B4FBE6500E8F1D6B02" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="104">Solanum rhizomatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where corollas vary from white to pale lilac even within single individuals. Label information from 
<emphasis id="C6DD94C411D7FE85F89FA2F38670BA48" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="104">Nee &amp; Mendoza 57594</emphasis>
notes changes in the corolla colour during development, where the corolla is white in bud, violet in anthesis, and darker after wilting.
</paragraph>
